={
  "model": "claude-sonnet-5",
  "max_tokens": 300,
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Grade this 1099 commission-sales applicant for a website-sales partner role on a 1.0-5.0 scale. Rubric: evidence of commission-only/1099 sales history (+1.5), B2B outbound/closing experience (+1.0), local-services or SMB market familiarity (+0.5), clear written communication in their answers (+0.5), explicit acceptance of the 72-hour first-dial activation window (+0.5). Base score 1.0. Salary-only history with no commission evidence caps the score at 2.0. Applicant data — Name: {{ $json.body.name }} · State requested: {{ $json.body.state }} · Sales background: {{ $json.body.background }} · Biggest commission close: {{ $json.body.biggest_close }} · Accepts 72-hour activation: {{ $json.body.accepts_72h }} · LinkedIn: {{ $json.body.linkedin }}. Reply with STRICT JSON only, no prose: {\"score\": <number>, \"reasons\": \"<one sentence>\"}"
    }
  ]
}

parameters.jsCode:
const applicant = $('Applicant Webhook').first().json.body;
let score = 0, reasons = 'ungraded';
try {
  const text = $json.content?.[0]?.text ?? '{}';
  const parsed = JSON.parse(text.replace(/^```json?\s*|```\s*$/g, ''));
  score = Number(parsed.score) || 0;
  reasons = String(parsed.reasons || '').slice(0, 250);
} catch (e) { reasons = 'grade-parse-failed: manual review'; }
const topTier = score >= 4.0;
return [{ json: { ...applicant, screen_score: score, screen_reasons: reasons, tier_tag: topTier ? 'Applicant: Top Tier' : 'Applicant: Manual Review' } }];
